1.text: Bend backward slightly while standing to stretch your back.

2.text: Stretch your back while lying on your stomach.

3.text: Do a standing side stretch to work on your whole body at once.

4.text: Touch your toes from a chair to stretch your upper body, back, and legs.

5.text: Work on a simple bound-angle stretch for your whole body.

6.text: Work on your shoulders and triceps.

7.text: Sit on the floor and extend your arms behind you to stretch your biceps.

8.text: Bend your hands up and down to extend your wrist muscles.

9.text: Face a corner to stretch your chest and back.

10.text: Do a reclined spinal twist to stretch your back.

11.text: Use a levator scapulae stretch for your neck.

12.text: Step forward to stretch your calf muscles.

13.text: Lift your leg behind and grab your foot to stretch your quadriceps.

14.text: Work on your hamstrings by grabbing the back of your legs.

15.text: Use the butterfly stretch for your legs and groin.
